Module SCRAME
Package edu.university.assessments

Interface Examinable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MainComponent, Subcomponent
    public interface Examinable
    Interface for examinable components. The reason behind such interface is, every examinable component, be it main component or subcomponent of a course must have the following:
    • The name of the component
    • A weight as of its parent component
    • A raw mark given by the professor
    • An overall mark (out of the maximum percentage of the component)
    This is for loose coupling.

    • Method Detail

      • getWeightage

        int getWeightage()
        This method is used to get the weight of an examinable component.
        Returns:
        an integer representing the weight of an examinable component (out of 100).

      • getRawMark

        double getRawMark()
        This method is used to get the raw mark of an exminable component. When implementing this method, note that not every examinable component has a raw mark. For example, coursework that has subcomponents do not have a rawmark by itself.
        Returns:
        a double type that is the raw mark (out of 100), as entered by the professor for a particular component in the case of a component that does not have subcomponents. And in the case of component having subcomponents, this will return the sum of marks of all subcomponents.

      • getMark

        double getMark()
        This method is used to get the mark of an examinable components. The implementation of this method needs to calculate the mark of the component as of the entire course.
        Returns:
        a double type that is the mark of the component, as of the entire course.

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        This method is used to get the name of an examinable component.
        Returns:
        the name of the examinable component.
